data.content: (Kỹ thuật) bị ép, bị nén

verb
-presses; -pressed; -pressing
to press or squeeze (something) so that it is smaller or fills less space [+ obj]
compress the air in a closed chamber
She compressed her lips. [no obj]
Her lips compressed into a frown.
a material that compresses easily
[+ obj] :to make (something) shorter or smaller
compress a chapter
The author compressed [=condensed] 80 years of history into 15 pages.
computers :to reduce the size of (a computer file) by using special software [+ obj]
compress a digital photograph [no obj]
This type of file compresses easily. - opposite decompress
noun
plural -presses
[count] :a folded cloth that is pressed against a part of the body to reduce pain or stop bleeding from an injury
a cold compress
